      <prompt>
        <p>Blood group antigens are usually found on red cells. There are 26 blood group systems, of which the most important in transfusion medicine are ABO and Rhesus.</p>
        <p>What antibodies are found in people with blood group O?</p>
      </prompt>
      <simpleChoice identifier="CHOICE_000">Anti-A</simpleChoice>
      <simpleChoice identifier="CHOICE_001">Anti-B</simpleChoice>
      <simpleChoice identifier="CHOICE_002">Anti-O</simpleChoice>
      <simpleChoice identifier="CHOICE_003">Anti-A and anti-B</simpleChoice>
      <simpleChoice identifier="CHOICE_004">None</simpleChoice>
    </choiceInteraction>
  </itemBody>
  <modalFeedback identifier="CORRECT_FEEDBACK" outcomeIdentifier="GENERAL_FEEDBACK" showHide="show">
    <p>
      <b>Option D (Anti-A and anti-B) is Correct.</b>
      Anti-A and anti-B antibodies are found in people with blood group O.
    </p>
